  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, you can spend 8 hours creating a @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete.5e-items.0HpKcXW6g9xvhSJm]{Transmuter's Stone} that stores transmutation magic. You can benefit from the stone yourself or give it to another creature. A creature gains a benefit of your choice as long as the stone is in the creature's possession. When you create the stone, choose the benefit from the following options:</p><ul><li><strong>Darkvision</strong> out to a range of 60 feet</li><li>An increase to speed of 10 feet while the creature is <strong>unencumbered</strong></li><li>Proficiency in Constitution saving throws</li><li><strong>Resistance</strong> to acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder damage (your choice whenever you choose this benefit)</li></ul><p>Each time you cast a <strong>transmutation</strong> spell of 1st level or higher, you can change the effect of your stone if the stone is on your person.</p><p>If you create a new transmuter's stone, the previous one ceases to function.</p>",
